# Runtime config for the `github-to-eat` CLI — the tracker you import INTO.
#
# Owner-role agent API key for the target EAT project (the one that will receive
# the imported stories). Mint it in the SPA under Project Settings -> API keys.
EAT_AGENT_KEY=

# Optional: override the API base URL (defaults to production).
# EAT_API_BASE=https://api.eastagiletracker.com/api/v1

# Optional: override the web app base URL used for the board link.
# EAT_APP_BASE=https://eastagiletracker.com

# Maintaining this tool itself? Its tracker credentials are separate and are NOT
# read by the CLI — see .env.dev.example.
